<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,327,712]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
DIAGNOSIS. Male: only Neotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[582,736,328,352]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Atrichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[582,736,328,352]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Atrichopogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with gonostylus reduced to small knob and sternite 
<number box="[1317,1331,327,351]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="9.0">9</number>
with two posterior lateral prongs, each bearing two strong apical bristles. Female, with the following combination of characters: with an elongate, sack-like, spermatheca; abdominal tergites 
<number box="[970,1011,399,423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
light brown and the remainder of the abdomen pale and postsutural area with darker spot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,327,712]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
DESCRIPTION. Male adult. Head: Pale brown. Ommatidia with interfacet pubescence, broadly abutting medially for length of 
<number box="[404,446,508,532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
ommatidia. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[699,761,508,532]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[197,1396,189,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[189,1413,171,1970]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Atrichopogon pachito sp. nov. Male. A, C; female. B, D. A – B, flagellum (flagellomeres I – VIII and IX – XIII), lateral view; C – D, palpus, lateral view. Scale bar 0.04 mm. Legends: third segment (3 er); sensorial pit (Sp)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[751,761,508,532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A) uniformly brown with plume setae well-developed; with 
<number box="[151,179,543,567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
flagellomeres separate, flagellomeres 
<number box="[613,669,543,567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
without plume setae, 
<number box="[918,946,543,567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="10.0">10</number>
longer than 
<number box="[1089,1105,543,567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="9.0">9</number>
, flagellomere 
<number box="[1267,1280,543,567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="9.0">9</number>
/ 
<number box="[1289,1316,543,567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="10.0">10</number>
<number box="[1324,1436,543,567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="0.66" valueMax="0.68" valueMin="0.64">0.64–0.68</number>
(
<number box="[159,212,580,604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="0.65">0.65</number>
, n= 
<number box="[262,275,580,604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
); flagellomeres 
<number box="[464,533,580,604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11–13</number>
elongate; flagellomere 
<number box="[812,840,580,604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
with apical projection not basally constricted; AR 
<number box="[151,263,615,639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="0.915" valueMax="0.93" valueMin="0.9">0.90–0.93</number>
(
<number box="[279,332,615,639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="0.91">0.91</number>
, n= 
<number box="[377,390,615,639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
). Palpus (
<figureCitation box="[501,564,615,639]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[197,1396,189,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[189,1413,171,1970]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Atrichopogon pachito sp. nov. Male. A, C; female. B, D. A – B, flagellum (flagellomeres I – VIII and IX – XIII), lateral view; C – D, palpus, lateral view. Scale bar 0.04 mm. Legends: third segment (3 er); sensorial pit (Sp)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[554,564,615,639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C) with segments 
<number box="[772,814,615,639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
pale, 
<number box="[883,924,615,639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
brown; third segment with subapical sensory pit opening on distal third; segments 4, 5 separate; PR 
<number box="[776,860,652,676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="2.35" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.1">2.1–2.6</number>
(
<number box="[876,915,652,676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="2.4">2.4</number>
, n= 
<number box="[961,974,652,676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
). Proboscis length 
<number box="[1191,1302,652,676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="0.11499999999999999" valueMax="0.12" valueMin="0.11">0.11–0.12</number>
(
<number box="[1318,1370,652,676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="0.11">0.11</number>
, n= 
<number box="[1415,1428,652,676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
) mm; head width/proboscis length 
<number box="[532,567,687,711]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="2.2">2.2</number>
(n= 
<number box="[617,631,687,711]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[598,801,1872,1893]" box="[598,801,1872,1893]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">sp. nov. A. B.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1938,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Thorax: Light brown. Scutum with setae arising directly from surface, not in pits; postsutural area with darker spot and some setae; with lateral suture; scutellum with four setae. Paratergite with one stout seta. Anepisternum narrow, broadly bilobed posteriorly.</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215474/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="23" targetBox="[167,1421,219,1782]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1822,1907]" pageId="3" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1822,1845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="23">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[291,517,1823,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Atrichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachito" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[291,517,1823,1845]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="23">Atrichopogon pachito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[528,611,1824,1845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="23" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Male. Genitalia. A, dorsal view; B, dorsolateral view, apex; C, lateral view. Legends: apical spine (A sp); gonocoxite (gx); lobe lateral sternite 9 (lo la st 9); seta 1 (s1); seta 2 (s2); seta 3 (s3); seta 4 (s4); tergite 9 (tg 9).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1951,2016]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,1713]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="3" pageNumber="23">
Wing: (Fig. 
<number box="[349,363,1951,1975]" pageId="3" pageNumber="23" value="2.0">2</number>
A) Plain, without pattern of pigmented membrane; with scattered macrotrichiae in apical portion of cells r 
<number box="[356,364,2002,2016]" pageId="3" pageNumber="23" value="3.0">3</number>
, m 
<number box="[406,414,2002,2016]" pageId="3" pageNumber="23" value="1.0">1</number>
; second radial cell 
<number box="[657,693,1986,2010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="23" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times longer than first; first radial cell reduced; wing length 
<number box="[151,265,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="0.73" valueMax="0.76" valueMin="0.7">0.70–0.76</number>
(
<number box="[281,336,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="0.74">0.74</number>
, n= 
<number box="[379,392,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
) mm; breadth 
<number box="[560,610,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="0.27">0.27</number>
(n= 
<number box="[660,673,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
) mm; CR 
<number box="[793,908,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="0.595" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.59">0.59–0.60</number>
(
<number box="[923,977,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="0.59">0.59</number>
, n= 
<number box="[1024,1038,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
). Halter pale. Legs uniformly light brown; hindtibia slightly expanded at apex. Hindtibial spur thick, length longer than width of hindtibia at midlength; hindtibial comb with 
<number box="[541,555,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="9.0">9</number>
spines; prothoracic 
<collectingCountry box="[798,834,224,247]" name="Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">TR</collectingCountry>
3.0– 
<number box="[896,931,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.5">3.5</number>
(
<number box="[950,990,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.2">3.2</number>
, n= 
<number box="[1039,1053,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
), mesothoracic 
<collectingCountry box="[1240,1276,224,247]" name="Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">TR</collectingCountry>
<number box="[1287,1372,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.05" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.4</number>
(
<number box="[1392,1431,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.1">3.1</number>
, n= 
<number box="[185,199,259,283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
), metathoracic 
<collectingCountry box="[380,416,260,283]" name="Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">TR</collectingCountry>
<number box="[427,513,259,283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="2.5" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.6</number>
(
<number box="[531,570,259,283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="2.5">2.5</number>
, n= 
<number box="[620,634,259,283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
); claws curved, moderately stout; empodia present. Abdomen: pale, with tergites 
<number box="[305,350,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
, sternites 
<number box="[470,513,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7</number>
brown, remaining tergites and sternites pale light. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1319,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1822,1845]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,219,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,203,1794]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Atrichopogon pachito sp. nov. Male. Genitalia. A, dorsal view; B, dorsolateral view, apex; C, lateral view. Legends: apical spine (A sp); gonocoxite (gx); lobe lateral sternite 9 (lo la st 9); seta 1 (s 1); seta 2 (s 2); seta 3 (s 3); seta 4 (s 4); tergite 9 (tg 9)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215474/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">
Figs. 
<number box="[1306,1319,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A–C, 
<number box="[1391,1406,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="4.0">4</number>
A) small (length 
<quantity box="[313,422,330,354]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.16">0.16 mm</quantity>
), tergite 
<number box="[526,540,330,354]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="9.0">9</number>
short, not extending to level of apex of gonocoxite, more or less triangular, swollen basally, basal arch low; posterior margin truncate; sternite 
<number box="[944,958,366,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="9.0">9</number>
extremely modified, with pair of lateral lobes connected medially, not extending to level apex of gonocoxite, swollen basally, tapering to apex, with pair thick apical spines, medial lobe small, not expanded posteriorly. Gonocoxite without medial lobe, swollen basally, tapering to apex, not extending to apex of aedeagal-parameral complex, gonocoxite length/width 
<number box="[151,237,509,533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="2.9000000000000004" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.1</number>
(
<number box="[252,292,509,533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="2.9">2.9</number>
, n= 
<number box="[336,349,509,533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
) mm; gonostylus small, reduced to hook-shaped lobe, with patch of thin spicules, 
<number box="[1288,1302,509,533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="4.0">4</number>
setae: (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[230,1371,185,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[214,1382,169,1900]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia, ventral view: A. Atrichopogon pachito sp. nov; B. Atrichopogon grogani sp. nov. Scale bar: A: 0.04 mm; B: 0.16 mm. Legends: aedeagal-parameral complex (Ae-Pa); apical spine (A sp); apodeme of gonocoxite (Ap gx); apodeme of sternite 9 (Ap t 9); base of tergite 9 (ba tg 9); gonocoxite (gx); lobe lateral of sternite 9 (lo la st 9); medial lobe of sternite 9 (me lo st 9); seta 1 (s 1); seta 2 (s 2); seta 3 (s 3); seta 4 (s 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215475/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,545,569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A), seta 
<number box="[262,278,545,569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="1.0">1</number>
: external margin with a long, curved seta; seta 
<number box="[820,838,545,569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="2.0">2</number>
: a distinctive, flame-shaped seta with bifid tip (only observed with Scanning Electron Microscope, 
<figureCitation box="[700,768,580,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1822,1845]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,219,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,203,1794]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Atrichopogon pachito sp. nov. Male. Genitalia. A, dorsal view; B, dorsolateral view, apex; C, lateral view. Legends: apical spine (A sp); gonocoxite (gx); lobe lateral sternite 9 (lo la st 9); seta 1 (s 1); seta 2 (s 2); seta 3 (s 3); seta 4 (s 4); tergite 9 (tg 9)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215474/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[755,768,580,604]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B); seta 
<number box="[905,922,580,604]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
: a medial thin, simple seta; seta 
<number box="[1312,1330,580,604]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="4.0">4</number>
: a small, stout seta with blunt apex. Aedeagal-parameral complex with thick lateral margins, bilobed posteriorly, with pair of small denticules; lateral arms slender, basal arch extending to 
<number box="[889,939,652,676]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="0.46">0.46</number>
of total length. Cercus lobe-like, extending beyond posterior margin of tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1713]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">
Female adult. As for male, with following differences. Antenna with flagellomeres 
<number box="[1155,1197,723,747]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="4.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="1.0">1–8</number>
longer than breadth; flagellomeres 
<number box="[317,373,759,783]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="11.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="9.0">9–13</number>
elongate, proportions as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[807,876,759,783]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[197,1396,189,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[189,1413,171,1970]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Atrichopogon pachito sp. nov. Male. A, C; female. B, D. A – B, flagellum (flagellomeres I – VIII and IX – XIII), lateral view; C – D, palpus, lateral view. Scale bar 0.04 mm. Legends: third segment (3 er); sensorial pit (Sp)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215473/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[865,876,759,783]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B, flagellomere 
<number box="[1075,1103,759,783]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="13.0">13</number>
with apical projection; AR 
<number box="[151,263,795,819]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="1.22" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.14">1.14–1.30</number>
(
<number box="[280,332,795,819]" pageId="4" pageNumber="24" value="1.23">1.23</number>
, n= 
